  "text": "high (expressing TLR11, -12, -13) and signal regulatory protein α (Sirp) high cDCs (expressing TLR13 but lacking TLR11, -12) responded to hiSa, whereas Tlr23479 -/-pDCs (expressing TLR12 but lacking TLR11, -13) failed to do so (Fig. 1G) . Together, these findings implied that TLR13 acts as bacterial single-stranded (ss) RNA sensor, even though TLR13 has recently been linked with the recognition of vesicular stomatitis virus [CITATION_1] .",
